content:
I have a JSON file containing information about the different continents on Earth. The structure of the file is as follows:
{
"continents": [
{
"name": "Asia",
"area": "44,579,000 km²",
"population": "4,463,235,000"
},
{
"name": "Africa",
"area": "30,370,000 km²",
"population": "1,295,480,000"
},
{
"name": "North America",
"area": "24,709,000 km²",
"population": "579,024,000"
},
{
"name": "South America",
"area": "17,840,000 km²",
"population": "422,535,000"
},
{
"name": "Antarctica",
"area": "14,000,000 km²",
"population": "0"
},
{
"name": "Europe",
"area": "10,180,000 km²",
"population": "747,447,000"
},
{
"name": "Australia/Oceania",
"area": "9,008,500 km²",
"population": "42,651,000"
}
]
}
Based on this data, how many continents are there on Earth?
